  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I import my Gmail contacts into Skype?",
  "response": "Importing your Gmail contacts into Skype is a straightforward process. Here's how you can do it:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Import Gmail Contacts into Skype (Desktop or Web App):**\n\n1. **Open Skype:**\n   - Launch the Skype application on your computer or go to [Skype's website](https://www.skype.com) and sign in to your account.\n\n2. **Go to Contacts:**\n   - In Skype, click on the **Contacts** tab (or section) in the left-hand menu.\n\n3. **Add or Import Contacts:**\n   - Look for an option like **Add Contact**, **Import Contacts**, or **Find People** and click on it.\n\n4. **Select Gmail:**\n   - You\u2019ll see options to import contacts from various platforms. Choose **Gmail**.\n\n5. **Sign in to Gmail:**\n   - A window will pop up asking you to sign in to your Google account. Enter your Gmail credentials and grant Skype permission to access your contacts.\n\n6. **Authorize Access:**\n   - Click **Allow** to give Skype access to your Gmail contacts.\n\n7. **Select Contacts to Import:**\n   - After granting access, Skype will display a list of your Gmail contacts. Select the ones you want to import and confirm.\n\n8. **Complete the Process:**\n   - Skype will now import your selected Gmail contacts. You should see them in your Skype contacts list after the process is complete.\n\n---\n\n### **Notes:**\n- If you don\u2019t see the option to import Gmail contacts directly, Skype may no longer support this feature. In that case, you can manually add contacts by searching for their email addresses.\n- Ensure you\u2019re using the latest version of Skype for the best experience.\n- If you\u2019re using Skype on a mobile device, the process may vary slightly, and importing Gmail contacts may not be supported directly.\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
